"***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"**\n1. Not very likely\n2. Somewhat likely\n3. Slightly likely\n4. Neutral or Uncertain\n5. Moderately likely\n6. Very likely\n7. Extremely likely\n\nBased on the passage, Bond has just been captured and disarmed by Le Chiffre and his gunmen. He has attempted to escape and fight back, but his actions have resulted in him being roughly searched and his only weapon, a fountain pen, being taken away. Le Chiffre seems to be aware of Bond's thoughts and is not giving him much chance to escape. Therefore, the likelihood of Bond escaping is not very high.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"**\n6. Very suspenseful\n7. Extremely suspenseful\n\nThe passage is suspenseful because it describes a high-stakes situation where Bond is trying to evade capture and communicate with Vesper while being closely watched and physically restrained by Le Chiffre's men. The action and the tension in the scene, along with the anticipation of what might happen next, create a sense of suspense."